Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, suggesting impaired renal function and possible nephrotic syndrome or diabetic ketoacidosis, though HbA1c is unexpectedly low. Urine is cloudy, brown, and ammoniacal, but no evidence of infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). Low serum CO₂ may indicate metabolic acidosis. Recommend urgent clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation for acute or chronic kidney disease and further assessment of metabolic status.
